## Quality Requirements
- The optimized image should feel dramatically more "dimensional" and professionally lit.
- Every enhancement must be physically plausible — the result should look like expert studio photography, not digital manipulation.
- Maintain natural color fidelity throughout all lighting adjustments.

## Constraints
- Do NOT move, add, or remove any object, furniture, or architectural element.
- Do NOT change material colors or textures — only how light interacts with them.
- Preserve the original composition and camera angle exactly.
- The overall mood should be enhanced and refined, not fundamentally changed.
- Output exactly one image with no accompanying text.